<section id="fs-idm325076304">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para id="fs-idm320923408">World War I propaganda did not always appear in the form of posters encouraging citizens to do their part for the effort. In fact, the Great War spawned one of the most famous patriotic tunes in the history of the United States, <emphasis effect="italics">Over There</emphasis>. Written by George M. Cohan immediately after Congress declared war against Germany, <emphasis effect="italics">Over There</emphasis> was performed by a variety of groups in the United States. Its lyrics encouraged men to join the military and defeat the Germans.</para>
